31/05/2004
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The UN war crimes tribunal's chief prosecutor, Carla del Ponte, begins a tour of BiH and Croatia on Monday (31 May).
In Banja Luka, she will meet with senior Republika Srpska officials to discuss the failure to co-operate with The Hague tribunal, the subject of strong criticism from the international community.
In other news, Principal Deputy High Representative to BiH Donald Hays warned on Sunday that the country could no longer afford to lose money due to poor management of public enterprises.
Presenting the results of a recent survey conducted by the Office of the High Representative, Hays said that despite ongoing reforms, the situation involving public companies remains critical.
(Pincom.info, Dnevni avaz - 31/05/04;
Fena, PBS BiH - 30/05/04)
